                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>N York</placeName>\n                <date>17<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Feby/61</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>\n                <placeName>Pha</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Rev Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">The bearer <persName>R'. Abraham<lb/> Nissan</persName> is come\n                among us to plead the<lb/> cause of our starving brethren at<lb/>\n                <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>. At no time neither the<lb/> memory of man has\n                their condition<lb/> been so pitiable as at present, and<lb/> especially in the\n                community which<lb/> he particularly represents, the<lb/> Ashkenazin Jerooshim.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">As he asks for nothing for<lb/> himself, but that every donation\n                be<lb/> sent to <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName> direct, I trust<lb/> you will\n                afford his mission your<lb/> powerful support, as well by your<lb/> exertions among\n                your friends as in<lb/> the columns of the Occident.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am Rev. Dr Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Very respectfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">MJRaphall</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3s17tc7c/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
